{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17645449","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17645449"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:18:11+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:18:11+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18114"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18114","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18114"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.06,0.26,0.69,0,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10828"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78290"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10828","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10828"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18114"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63685"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7229"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25201"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25204"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26857"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78290","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78290"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThere are a number of nerves that innervate the arm.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following innervates the anterior compartment?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Axillary","Median","Musculocutaneous","Radial","Ulnar"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Emusculocutaneous nerve\u003C/strong\u003E innervates the muscles of the anterior compartment of the arm, which include the biceps brachii, brachialis, and coracobrachialis. These muscles are primarily responsible for flexion at the elbow and supination of the forearm. The patient\u0027s symptoms of weakness in elbow flexion and forearm supination suggest an issue with the musculocutaneous nerve.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eradial nerve\u003C/strong\u003E innervates the posterior compartment of the arm and forearm, which is responsible for extension of the elbow, wrist, and fingers. It does not innervate the anterior compartment of the arm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eulnar nerve\u003C/strong\u003E primarily innervates the intrinsic muscles of the hand and some muscles in the forearm. It does not innervate the anterior compartment of the arm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Emedian nerve\u003C/strong\u003E innervates most of the flexor muscles in the forearm and some muscles in the hand, but it does not innervate the anterior compartment of the arm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eaxillary nerve\u003C/strong\u003E innervates the deltoid and teres minor muscles, which are involved in shoulder abduction and external rotation. It does not innervate the anterior compartment of the arm.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The musculocutaneous nerve innervates the muscles of the anterior compartment of the arm.","The anterior compartment of the arm includes the biceps brachii, brachialis, and coracobrachialis muscles.","The musculocutaneous nerve is responsible for flexion at the elbow and supination of the forearm."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Miniato MA, Anand P, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725618","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30521257","Paulsen, F., \u0026 Waschke, J. (Eds.). (2023). Sobotta Atlas of Anatomy, Vol. 1, English/Latin: General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System (Vol. 1). Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63685"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18114"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63685","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63685"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-10T11:53:30+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-10T11:54:01+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10828"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78290"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","posit